 <div class="slide" data-slide="4" data-part="1"><h2 class="big-q">🧪 Demo: Cup-in-Water Trick</h2><p class="lead">Try this: stuff a paper towel in the bottom of a cup. Push the cup UPSIDE-DOWN into water.</p><ul class="checklist"><li>Pull it out — paper towel is DRY!</li><li>Why? AIR was inside the cup. It blocked water from getting in.</li><li>Air takes up SPACE — it pushes water away.</li></ul><div class="callout">💡 Air is a real substance — it occupies space.</div></div>
 <div class="slide" data-slide="5" data-part="1"><h2 class="big-q">⚖️ Demo: Air Has WEIGHT</h2><p class="lead">Get 2 identical balloons. Tie them on a stick like a balance.</p><ul class="checklist"><li>Pop one balloon (let air out).</li><li>The empty side rises! The full side sinks down.</li><li>Why? The full balloon has more AIR — and air HAS weight.</li></ul><div class="callout">💡 Air is heavier than nothing — every breath weighs something!</div></div>
