 <div class="slide" data-slide="5" data-part="1"><h2 class="big-q">🔬 The 3 States of Matter</h2><div class="flow"><div>🧊<span class="label">Solid (packed close)</span></div><span class="arrow">→</span><div>💧<span class="label">Liquid (loose)</span></div><span class="arrow">→</span><div>💨<span class="label">Gas (far apart)</span></div></div><div class="callout">💡 Same particles — different SPACING!</div></div>
 <div class="slide" data-slide="6" data-part="1"><h2 class="big-q">🔍 What Makes Each State Different?</h2><div class="reveal-grid"><div class="reveal"><b>🧊 Solid</b><br>Particles are STUCK together and packed tight. Can't flow.</div><div class="reveal"><b>💧 Liquid</b><br>Particles can SLIDE past each other. Flows but stays together.</div><div class="reveal"><b>💨 Gas</b><br>Particles ZOOM around freely. Far apart. Fills any container.</div></div><p class="small">Tap each box!</p></div>
 <div class="slide" data-slide="7" data-part="1"><h2 class="big-q">🌬 Demo: Smell Across the Room</h2><p class="lead">Open a smelly thing (vanilla, perfume, popcorn) on one side. Walk to the other side.</p><ul class="checklist"><li>You can SMELL it — even far away!</li><li>Why? Tiny particles ZOOMED through the air to your nose.</li><li>Gas particles move FAST and SPREAD OUT.</li></ul><div class="callout">💡 You're literally smelling tiny particles bumping into you!</div></div>
